# Migration Walkthrough: TensorFlow → PyTorch

## Summary

Migrated the entire **multisensory** audio-visual scene analysis codebase from TensorFlow 1.x (with `tf-slim`) to PyTorch 2.x. Created **25 files** across **8 packages** under `multisensory_pytorch/`.

---

## Project Structure Created

```
multisensory_pytorch/          # 25 files total
├── models/                    # Neural network architectures
│   ├── blocks.py              # Block2D, Block3D, Conv2dSame, Conv3dSame
│   ├── shift_net.py           # ShiftNet (3D ResNet + sound CNN + merge)
│   ├── sourcesep.py           # SourceSep U-Net (9 enc + 8 dec + video conditioning)
│   └── discriminator.py       # Patch-based spectrogram GAN discriminator
├── losses/
│   ├── separation.py          # L1 spec/phase loss, PIT loss
│   ├── adversarial.py         # GAN sigmoid loss
│   └── classification.py      # Label smoothing CE, binary classification
├── datasets/
│   ├── shift_dataset.py       # ShiftNet dataset (frames + audio dirs)
│   └── sep_dataset.py         # Separation dataset (paired video mixing)
├── training/
│   ├── train_sep.py           # Source separation training loop (AMP, DDP-ready)
│   └── train_shift.py         # ShiftNet training loop
├── inference/
│   └── sep_video.py           # Video source separation CLI
├── utils/
│   ├── audio.py               # STFT/iSTFT, Griffin-Lim, dB, normalization
│   ├── params.py              # Params class + all config presets
│   └── misc.py                # CheckpointManager, moving_avg, Timer
├── scripts/
│   └── convert_weights.py     # TF checkpoint → PyTorch .pt converter
└── requirements.txt
```

