## Key Design Decisions

1. **TF SAME padding** — Implemented [_pad_same_nd()](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Development/Python_Projects/AI/multisensory/multisensory_pytorch/models/blocks.py#41-59) in [blocks.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Development/Python_Projects/AI/multisensory/multisensory_pytorch/models/blocks.py) for asymmetric padding when stride > 1, matching TF behavior exactly
2. **Batch norm** — Explicitly set `momentum=0.0003` and `eps=0.001` everywhere (TF defaults differ from PyTorch)
3. **Weight init** — UNet layers use `normal_(0, 0.02)` matching TF's `random_normal_initializer`
4. **Fractional max pooling** — Uses `F.fractional_max_pool2d` during training and `F.adaptive_max_pool2d` during eval for deterministic inference
5. **STFT** — `center=False` to match TF's `pad_end=False`; transpose from [(batch, freq, frames)](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Development/Python_Projects/AI/multisensory/src/shift_dset.py#81-84) to [(batch, frames, freq)](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Development/Python_Projects/AI/multisensory/src/shift_dset.py#81-84) to match TF layout

