## How to Use

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r multisensory_pytorch/requirements.txt
```

### 2. Convert existing TF weights
```bash
# List TF checkpoint variables
python -m multisensory_pytorch.scripts.convert_weights \
    --tf_checkpoint ../results/nets/shift/net.tf-650000 \
    --output shift_net.pt --model_type shift --list_vars

# Convert ShiftNet weights
python -m multisensory_pytorch.scripts.convert_weights \
    --tf_checkpoint ../results/nets/shift/net.tf-650000 \
    --output shift_net.pt --model_type shift

# Convert SourceSep weights
python -m multisensory_pytorch.scripts.convert_weights \
    --tf_checkpoint ../results/nets/sep/full/net.tf-160000 \
    --output sourcesep_full.pt --model_type sourcesep
```

### 3. Run inference
```bash
python -m multisensory_pytorch.inference.sep_video \
    path/to/video.mp4 --weights sourcesep_full.pt --out results/ --gpu 0
```

### 4. Train from scratch
```bash
# Source separation
python -m multisensory_pytorch.training.train_sep --model full --gpu 0

# ShiftNet
python -m multisensory_pytorch.training.train_shift --gpu 0
```
